\section{Related Work}
\label{sec:related}
% ============================================================================

\begin{table}[H]
\centering
\caption{Comparison of NLP testing and localization approaches.}
\label{tab:related}
\small
\begin{tabular}{@{}p{2cm}cccccc@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Tool} & \rotatebox{70}{\textbf{Localize}} & \rotatebox{70}{\textbf{Per-stage}} & \rotatebox{70}{\textbf{Shrink}} & \rotatebox{70}{\textbf{Grammar}} & \rotatebox{70}{\textbf{Coverage}} & \rotatebox{70}{\textbf{Atlas}} \\
\midrule
CheckList & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
TextFlint & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & Part & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
Rob.\ Gym & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
TextAttack & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
NL-Augmenter & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & Part & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
METAL & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
LangTest & $\times$ & Partial & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
Grammarinator & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\checkmark$ & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
TreeReduce & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\checkmark$ & $\times$ & $\times$ & $\times$ \\
\textbf{MetamorF.} & $\checkmark$ & $\checkmark$ & $\checkmark$ & $\checkmark$ & $\checkmark$ & $\checkmark$ \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\textbf{CheckList}~\cite{ribeiro2020checklist} introduced behavioral testing for NLP with template-based test generation. It provides excellent test coverage analysis but no per-stage instrumentation or fault localization.

\textbf{TextFlint}~\cite{gui2021textflint} offers a unified robustness evaluation platform with task-specific transformations. It supports more transformations than CheckList but remains end-to-end.

\textbf{Robustness Gym}~\cite{goel2021robustness} provides a framework for evaluating model robustness with subpopulation analysis. It supports pipeline evaluation but not per-stage fault localization.

\textbf{TextAttack}~\cite{morris2020textattack} focuses on adversarial attacks against single models, not multi-stage pipeline testing.

\textbf{NL-Augmenter}~\cite{dhole2021nlaugmenter} provides 117+ community-contributed transformations. We use 8 of these as a starting point for our 15 transformations, extending them with grammar-awareness and composition tracking.

\textbf{SBFL for traditional software}~\cite{jones2002visualization,abreu2009spectrum} is well-studied but does not address NLP-specific challenges: linguistic ``coverage'' (not statement coverage), intermediate representations (parse trees, not memory states), and the introduction/amplification distinction.

\textbf{Delta debugging}~\cite{zeller2002simplifying} and \textbf{TreeReduce}~\cite{herfert2017treereduce} perform input minimization but do not maintain natural language grammaticality constraints.


% ============================================================================
\section{Threats to Validity}
\label{sec:threats}
% ============================================================================

\textbf{Internal validity.} Fault injection may not perfectly model real NLP bugs. We mitigate this by also evaluating on real bugs found during the case studies (Experiments 5--6).

\textbf{External validity.} Our evaluation covers spaCy, Stanza, HuggingFace, and Flair. Results may not generalize to proprietary cloud NLP APIs (AWS Comprehend, Google Cloud NLP) where intermediate representations are inaccessible. The generic adapter supports any Python pipeline with stage boundaries, but cloud APIs require special treatment.

\textbf{Construct validity.} The interventional causal analysis assumes meaning preservation, which is the hypothesis under test. We frame this as a validated heuristic and measure its accuracy empirically on fault-injected ground truth.

\textbf{Grammar coverage.} Our unification grammar covers 98.7\% of English inflectional forms but may miss rare constructions. Generated sentences are constrained to 2$\times$ Penn Treebank perplexity, which excludes some valid but unusual sentences.


% ============================================================================
\section{Conclusion}
\label{sec:conclusion}
% ============================================================================

\textsc{MetamorFault} transforms NLP pipeline debugging from end-to-end pass/fail testing into precise, per-stage fault localization with minimal counterexamples. The causal-differential analysis achieves 89.2\% localization accuracy, distinguishing fault introduction from amplification---a capability no existing NLP testing tool provides. Grammar-aware shrinking produces counterexamples 73\% smaller than the original while maintaining 100\% grammaticality. The behavioral atlas provides the NLP community with the first systematic cross-pipeline robustness database.

The key insight is that NLP pipeline faults have \emph{causal structure}: they originate at specific stages and propagate through intermediate representations. By instrumenting this structure and applying interventional analysis, we obtain diagnostic information qualitatively different from---and complementary to---existing end-to-end metamorphic testing.

\subsection*{Data Availability}
The grammar specification, transformation implementations, behavioral atlas, and evaluation scripts are available at \url{https://github.com/metamorfault/metamorfault}. All pipeline models use publicly available checkpoints.


